# Start Your Lab
Objective: Verify that all required applications are running.

Commands:

docker ps
docker start <dvwa_container_id>
docker start <juice_shop_container_id>
docker logs <dvwa_container_id>
docker logs <juice_shop_container_id>

Verify:
DVWA → http://localhost
Juice Shop → http://localhost:3000

# Reflected XSS (DVWA)
Objective: Understand how reflected input is displayed.

Steps:
Open the Reflected XSS page.
Set DVWA security to Low.
Enter normal text (e.g., Hello).
Observe how it is reflected.
Repeat on Medium and High.

Record:
Request
Response
HTML output
Security level differences

# Stored XSS (DVWA)
Objective: Understand how stored user input is displayed.

Steps:
Open the Stored XSS page.
Submit benign text (e.g., "Testing guestbook").
Refresh the page.
Observe how the content is stored and displayed.
Compare behavior across Low, Medium, and High.

Record:
Where the data is stored
How it is rendered
Differences between security levels

# Inspect Requests with Burp Suite
Objective: Analyze HTTP traffic.

Steps:
Enable Intercept.
Submit data to DVWA.

Observe:
Method
URL
Headers
Cookies
Parameters
Forward the request.

# Burp Repeater
Objective: Learn request replay.

Steps:
Send the captured request to Repeater.
Modify non-sensitive input (for example, change the guestbook message).
Send again.
Compare responses.

Record:
Original request
Modified request
Response differences

